RACE.FOOTNOTES: RED LABEL allowed to sprint to the lead, was in hand on the turn, put to urging upper stretch, widened command and was kept to task to the final sixteenth. STORMIN EL PRADO moved clear for second from inside on the turn, was no match for RED LABEL when set down for the drive, began to wear down inside the last eighth but lasted for the place. COPPER CROSSING was settled to the back after his break, picked up his pace from inside on the turn, fanned out to path three entering the lane, showed a willingness to run late, came up short for second but was easily best of the others. ARGYBARGY BUCK was just off the inside on the turn, floated out to path five into the stretch and ran evenly. MIDNIGHT JOKER chased from outside, took the bend three then four wide and had no late bid. CALL ME DROSSEL pressed RED LABEL from just outside, began to yield as he drifted out through the turn and continued to give way for the drive.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY MORNING GAL bumped with TRIPLE SCOUT at the break, stalked the early leader from between rivals, gradually angled in as others dropped back as she went for the lead on the bend, moved clear into the lane, took the inside and held sway under steady handling. ORNERY ANGEL raced in the second flight just off the inside, gained the rail on the turn, fanned out some for a clear path into the stretch and gradually edged ahead for second as she closed the gap just outside MY MORNING GAL in the late going. TRIPLE SCOUT bumped with MY MORNING GAL at the start, raced in contention from outside, also gradually angled in as she progressed through the bend, fought for second three wide in the lane but could not sustain her bid in the waning yards. ROCK THE BIRDHOUSE advanced two wide on the turn, angled outside TRIPLE SCOUT for a clear path upper stretch and showed a willingness to run late. WILDCAT BOBBIE dwelt at the start then broke inward, was slow to find her stride, lost ground staying well off the inside taking the turn, angled inside NEXT TIME YOU WIN midstretch and also showed some late interest. HELEN MAE'S SONG broke on top but was soon prompting the pace between horses, gradually angled in, as well, as she vied for the lead on the bend, did not stay with MY MORNING GAL leaving the turn and gave way through the stretch. NEXT TIME YOU WIN was shuffled back from tight quarters midway on the backstretch, advanced four wide on the turn, drifted out some at the top of the stretch and steadily faded. GHAALEB'S DOMAIN was away slowly, rushed up to the lead from inside but gave way before finishing three furlongs.
